      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism is a deeply divisive and often extreme ideology that has historically led to conflict and oppression. While some proponents argue it fosters social cohesion, the reality is that it often promotes an \"us versus them\" mentality, which is inherently dangerous. A functional society requires a commitment to shared values and rights that transcends narrow nationalistic boundaries. Therefore, the dangers of unchecked nationalism far outweigh any perceived benefits to social cohesion.",
