      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that a purely \"global citizen\" mindset would cause social bonds to fall apart is a romanticized view of human nature. National identity provides a necessary, tangible framework for collective action and mutual obligation. However, this sense of duty must be rooted in democratic principles and shared civic values, not in exclusionary ethnic nationalism. True social cohesion comes from shared governance and respect for law, not from tribalistic fervor.",
      "source": "target",
